# Syncthing ignore patterns for the deepmarks project.
#
# Keeps machine-specific junk + build artifacts + secrets out of the
# sync. Pattern syntax is similar to .gitignore but rooted at the
# shared folder. See https://docs.syncthing.net/users/ignoring.html.
#
# Keep in sync (no pun) with .gitignore — anything git won't commit
# should also not be Syncthing-synced across laptops / desktops, since
# Syncthing would otherwise churn on regenerated files and propagate
# sync-conflict-* artifacts between machines.

# ── Build outputs (regenerated per machine; syncing them causes conflicts) ──
**/node_modules
**/build
**/dist
**/.svelte-kit
**/.vite
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# ── Test / coverage output ──
**/coverage
**/.nyc_output

# ── OS junk ──
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# ── Syncthing's own conflict files — never propagate these ──
.sync-conflict-*
**/.sync-conflict-*

# ── Editor state ──
.idea/
.vscode/
.cursor/
**/*.swp
**/*.swo

# ── Claude Code state ──
.claude/
**/.claude/

# ── Dev logs + process state ──
.dev-logs/
**/*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# ── Secrets — NEVER sync these between machines ──
# Box SSH targets, real IPs, nsecs, macaroons, and any .env file live
# on one machine only. Copy them manually when provisioning a new
# laptop so they never touch Syncthing's network path.
.env
**/.env
.env.*
**/.env.*
!.env.example
!**/.env.example
!.env.production
!**/.env.production
*.macaroon
**/*.macaroon
*nsec*
**/*nsec*
*secret*
**/*secret*
*.pem
**/*.pem
redis.txt
deploy/.env.local

# ── Operator-only notes (real IPs, personal specifics) ──
# docs/private/* is gitignored for the same reason; avoid syncing too
# so a shared laptop doesn't reveal it to a secondary device.
docs/private
!docs/private/README.md.example
